item.description:
Feel like you are in Ireland and enjoy great Celtic music by the Blackstone Valley Celtic Festival

Céad míle fáilte romhat: A Hundred Thousand Welcomes Before You!
Great music, food, entertainment, and a Celtic Village of arts and crafts.

List of Performers:
Fiddlers 3
Fergus (A five piece contemporary Irish group from Worcester, Massachusetts.
The Gobshtes
Jug O'Punch
The McInerney School of Irish Step Dancing
The Worcester Fire Brigade Pipes & Drums

In addition to great music, enjoy the Village of all things Celtic, dance, and traditional food and fare in a pub-style atmosphere! All on beautiful Webster Lake.

Meet at 10:30 am to get our seats, check out the lake, and for fun socializing before the show begins at 11 am. Meeting Location: As soon as you enter the ranch (after getting your tickets), meet at the picnic table on the right. If you come later and can't find us, call my cell: 508-381-1529.

Cost is $15 (plus $2.50 service charge) in advance or at the door.
There is also plenty of food and drinks available for purchase.
Please check out the rules on what you can and cannot bring into the ranch, etc.
item.name: Celtic Festival at Indian Ranch
